<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-07T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-07T16:00:00-05:00" n="152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">860d.01/24: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                        Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-07T22:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">May 7,
                                            1919, 10 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received May 7, 9.40 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>2031. Your 1880, May 6th, midnight. Have to-day telegraphed American
                                Consul, Helsingfors, quoting portions of American Mission’s number
                                1992, of May 5th, 8 p.m., and-instructing him to inform the Finnish
                                Government of the recognition of Finland. Lansing.</p>
                            <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">American Mission</hi></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>